    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Seen in the Yingzao fashi (1103 CE), referring to squared beams (fang 方) carved with bracket-arms in low relief, layered within the wall plane above pillar tops. Also called “superficial bracket arms” (fubigong).</Note_Text>
